<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She's usually known for being a regular on the catwalk.</p>

<p>But Jodie Kidd swapped her high heeled pumps for pints and punters on Thursday as she got behind the bar of the Three Colts Pub In Buckhurst Hill, Essex to raise money for charity.</p>

<p>The model, 41, who owns her own pub in West Sussex, opted for 70s-inspired flared jeans as she chatted to the pub's owner before heading behind the bar to pose for more snaps.</p>

<p>Barmaid in the making: Jodie Kidd, 41, got behind the bar of the Three Colts Pub In Buckhurst Hill, Essex to raise money for charity on Thursday</p>

<p>Jodie displayed her famous physique in a simple but stylish ensemble as she donned a casual white t-shirt and blue flared jeans.</p>

<p>The star teamed her look with a boho-inspired jacket and necklaces as she spoke to the owner behind the bar.</p>

<p>Jodie proved she was a natural barmaid by demonstrating her pint-pulling skills before posing for more snaps outside the pub.</p>

<p>The star took part in the shoot to raise funds for the LT Charity, which supports those who work in the licensed drink trade, including pubs and bars, many of which have struggled in recent months due to the COVID-19 pandemic.</p>

